Pre-Game Insights: Australia have already sewn up progression to round three and may field an unfamiliar lineup.
Bangladesh are rock-bottom of Group I with just one point to their name thus far.
Australia have four wins from four matches and are well on their way to the 2026 finals.
Bangladesh have never appeared at a World Cup and their only Asian Cup came back in 1980.
Australia received a bye through the first phase and began their bid to reach a sixth straight global finals with a 7-0 thrashing of Bangladesh.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia can expect to wrap up top spot in Group I with the minimum of fuss.
The Socceroos scored seven times in November's reverse fixture, but as they are already qualified and may field an unfamiliar lineup, the outcome could be a little less spectacular in Dhaka.
